<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,338,797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,423,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
In the protologue it is not mentioned the herbarium in which the type of 
<emphasis box="[1250,1400,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Pittier 12324</emphasis>
was allocated. According to the code (Art. 7.11, note 2, ex. 13), when the herbarium was not mentioned, all specimens of that gathering are 
<typeStatus box="[345,443,411,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">syntypes</typeStatus>
and, therefore, a 
<typeStatus box="[647,750,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">lectotype</typeStatus>
must be designated. Berg &amp; DeWolf (1975) were the first to name the material deposited in the NY herbarium as the 
<typeStatus box="[774,877,446,472]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">lectotype</typeStatus>
(in that work as “isotype”) and, therefore, must be followed (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[252,478,482,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" refId="ref7456" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="proceedings" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[351,410,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 7.11). Berg &amp; Villavicencio (2004) and Berg (2007) cite the VEN collection as a type (in these works as “ 
<typeStatus box="[440,547,518,545]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
”), but this must be corrected to the designation of Berg &amp; DeWolf (1975). The duplicate deposited at VEN has a label and a stamp called “ 
<typeStatus box="[791,903,554,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Holotype</typeStatus>
”, however, according to the code, the designation of a type is achieved only by effective publication (Art. 7.10). The code also warns that some of the material used by an author to describe a taxon may not be in the author’s herbarium (Art. 9A.1). Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Pittier, H. F." box="[1095,1238,626,652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="44 - 80" refId="ref7155" refString="Pittier, H. F. (1937) Ensayo sobre la classificacion de las especies venezolanas del genero Ficus. Boletin de la sociedad venezolana de ciencias naturales 4: 44 - 80." type="journal article" year="1937">Pittier (1937</bibRefCitation>
, Introduction) says that many materials have been accumulated in the VEN herbarium, it is not possible to be sure that the type belongs to the herbarium. There are cases in Pittier’s work that the types were not found at VEN (ex.: 
<taxonomicName authority="Pittier [1943: 257]" authorityName="Pittier" authorityPageNumber="257" authorityYear="1943" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corpulenta">
<emphasis box="[1185,1376,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Ficus corpulenta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pittier, H. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="257 - 260" refId="ref7190" refString="Pittier, H. F. (1943) Notas dendrologicas de Venezuela, Moraceae. Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Ciencias Naturales 8: 257 - 260." type="journal article" year="1943">Pittier [1943: 257]</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pederneiras, L. C. &amp; Romaniuc-Neto, S. &amp; Mansano, V. D. F." box="[281,543,734,760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="244 - 250" refId="ref6730" refString="Pederneiras, L. C., Romaniuc-Neto, S. &amp; Mansano, V. D. F. (2018) Nomenclatural revision of Ficus sect. Americanae (Moraceae): typification of Ficus americana and allied species. Phytotaxa 361: 244 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 361.2.9" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pederneiras 
<emphasis box="[419,475,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,338,797]" box="[189,1160,770,797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
